  "text": "Cadmium (Cd) is classified as a highly toxic environmental pollutant to the humans and animals. Caffeic acid phenyl ester (CAPE) is a biological active component of honeybee propolis extracts with potent free radical scavenger and antioxidant activity [CITATION_1] . This study was designed to investigate the effect of CAPE on some hematological parameters, blood coagulation, and hepatorenal functional status in cadmium (Cd) intoxication in rats. The results showed the remarkable protective effect of CAPE against Cd-induced hepatorenal injury with marked hematological and blood hemostasis disturbances in rats.",
